Regardless of who wins, the result – assuming we get one on election night – will ease some of the uncertainty businesses have been struggling with. An Obama victory would set up an instant battle over whether to keep or kill the tax cuts and spending, Lauricella notes. Headlines.Author: CBS.MarketWatch.com
Headlines.Headline: NewsWatch: Summary of business news

PARAGRAPH.#text:
NEW YORK (CBS.MW) -- The Nasdaq put on a nice performance in afternoon dealings Friday
    after coming under another round of selling pressure earlier in the session thanks to an
    improvement in some of the tech heavyweights. Quarter-end window dressing helped propel
    many of the big-name tech stocks, underpinning the Nasdaq. The Internet sector remained
    the biggest drag on the Nasdaq while networking and chip stocks rose. In the broader
    market, paper, drug and biotech shares rose while retail and oil service shares fell.
    Financial shares recovered nicely after slumping earlier in the session.
